					<description><![CDATA[<p>Learn how to optimize your TikTok videos and account to get more views and followers on TikTok and beyond.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-seo">TikTok SEO: 5 Tips to Own TikTok Search Results</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Here‚Äôs a little secret about TikTok fame and fortune: pumping out hilariously addictive video clips is only half the battle. To get your content in front of a big audience, grow your follower count, and mayhaps even go viral (<img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f632.png" alt="üò≤" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />), you need to understand TikTok SEO.</p>
<p>‚ÄúWait, like the search engine optimization I use to get my website on the front page of a Google search?‚Äù you ask.</p>
<p>Yep, that SEO. Well, there are a few key differences, which we‚Äôll explain in this guide.</p>
<p>There‚Äôs much to cover, so let‚Äôs dig in and start boosting those TikTok stats!</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#what-is-tiktok-seo">What is TikTok SEO?</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-does-content-discovery-happen-on-tiktok">How does content discovery happen on TikTok?</a></li>
<li><a href="#why-does-tiktok-seo-matter">Why does TikTok SEO matter?</a></li>
<li><a href="#what-are-the-tiktok-seo-ranking-factors">What are the TikTok SEO ranking factors?</a></li>
<li><a href="#5-ways-to-improve-your-tiktok-seo">5 ways to improve your TikTok SEO</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="what-is-tiktok-seo"></div>
<h2>What is TikTok SEO?</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/category/tiktok">TikTok</a> SEO is the practice of optimizing your content, account, and posts so they become more visible and discoverable on TikTok. In theory, it‚Äôs similar to any other form of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/seo">optimization</a> when the goal is to help your content surface more often when people search for relevant search terms.</p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-trailer-results.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok search results" width="356" height="578" class="aligncenter wp-image-84607 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-trailer-results.webp 356w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-trailer-results-185x300.webp 185w" sizes="(max-width: 356px) 100vw, 356px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>If you sell travel trailers, you want your content to end up in TikTok‚Äôs search results for that term.</em></p>
<p>In practice, TikTok SEO <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-competitors">differs from SEO on Google</a> because content discovery on TikTok differs from content <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/outdated-seo-tactics">discovery on Google</a>. In fact, it‚Äôs way more interesting!</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f680.png" alt="üöÄ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Free guide &gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/first-page-of-google?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_10WaysFirstPageGoogle_Download">10 Tangible &amp; Free Ways to Get on the First Page of Google</a></p>
<div id="how-does-content-discovery-happen-on-tiktok"></div>
<h2>How does content discovery happen on TikTok?</h2>
<p>To understand how TikTok SEO works (and how to make it work for you!), you need to understand the three ways people discover new content on the platform.</p>
<h3>The FYP page</h3>
<p>The<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/10/07/how-to-get-on-tiktok-fyp"> For You Page</a> is the secret sauce of new content discovery on TikTok. When anyone opens the app, they see a full-screen video they haven‚Äôt seen before. The content updates for every new session and is unique to every user.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-captions.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok FYP" width="366" height="579" class="aligncenter wp-image-84608 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-captions.webp 366w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-captions-190x300.webp 190w" sizes="(max-width: 366px) 100vw, 366px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>The FYP is where people can randomly discover your brand on TikTok.</em></p>
<p>The <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-algorithm">TikTok algorithm</a> decides which videos to show on each FYP. Since TikTok wants to keep you on the app longer, the algorithm will show content it thinks you‚Äôll like based on your prior behavior.</p>
<p>This is the main difference between TikTok SEO and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/local-seo-checklist/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google SEO</a>. TikTok promotes passive discovery, prioritizing each user‚Äôs behavior to guide it. Google focuses on active discovery since you have to tell it what you want before it shows you anything. That makes your current behavior (the words you type into the search bar) paramount on Google.</p>
<p>Okay, there is some<a href="https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/12412910?hl=en#:~:text=Personalization%20is%20only%20used%20in,personalized%20while%20others%20aren%27t." target="_blank" rel="noopener"> personalization in Google results</a>, but it‚Äôs not nearly as big a factor there as it is in the FYP.</p>
<h3>TikTok search</h3>
<p>Here‚Äôs where TikTok SEO and Google SEO start to overlap (and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-competitors">even compete</a>). At the top of the TikTok screen, there‚Äôs a search bar where you can type in a query, just like you would with a traditional search engine. There‚Äôs even an auto-suggest function that‚Äôll fill in popular keywords once you start typing.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-search-suggestions-makeup.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok search bar" width="543" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-84609 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-search-suggestions-makeup.webp 543w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-search-suggestions-makeup-480x530.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 543px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>TikTok has a search function that works much like Google‚Äôs</em></p>
<p>For the search function, the TikTok algorithm works a lot like Google‚Äôs. It looks for content that matches the keyword you‚Äôve typed in. Only on TikTok, there are a few different ways you can use keywords to your advantage. We‚Äôll get to those in a bit.</p>
<p>Once you‚Äôve entered your query, you get a page like this, with a scrollable list of videos to choose from.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-tutorial.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok search results for makup tutorial." width="349" height="584" class="aligncenter wp-image-84610 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-tutorial.webp 349w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-tutorial-179x300.webp 179w" sizes="(max-width: 349px) 100vw, 349px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>If you use keywords effectively, people will find your videos when they search for relevant terms.</em></p>
<p>Notice something else along the top of the page? You can search for content in several ways, like by hashtag, location, and even sound. That‚Äôll be important when we get into how to use TikTok SEO to rank your content.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Use the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/keywords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Keywords_KWTool">Free Keyword Tool</a> to find popular keywords you can use to rank on Google and TikTok</p>
<h3>Google Search</h3>
<p>Here‚Äôs where the two SEO worlds really collide. TikTok content is <a href="https://www.socialmediatoday.com/news/tiktok-is-fast-becoming-a-key-search-and-discovery-platform-for-younger-aud/629718/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">showing up in some Google search results</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-google-serp.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok videos showing in Google results." width="883" height="482" class="aligncenter wp-image-84611 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-google-serp.webp 883w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-google-serp-480x262.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 883px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Look at that! TikTok videos competing with Google‚Äôs own YouTube content in search results.</em></p>
<p>What does that mean? Your TikTok SEO strategy must align with your search engine SEO strategy to maximize your content&#8217;s visibility.</p>
<div id="why-does-tiktok-seo-matter"></div>
<h2>Why does TikTok SEO matter?</h2>
<p>TikTok has over <a href="https://backlinko.com/tiktok-users" target="_blank" rel="noopener">1 billion</a>(!) monthly active users. Even better, younger shoppers (the ones with rapidly increasing buying power) are <a href="https://www.emarketer.com/content/gen-z-prefers-tiktok-google-searches" target="_blank" rel="noopener">turning to TikTok over Google</a> to find new brands and products. A successful TikTok SEO strategy will get you in front of this huge and energetic group of buyers.</p>
<h3>TikTok is transforming into a search engine</h3>
<p>TikTok is still a discovery platform that helps users stumble on creators they‚Äôve never heard of. But as we mentioned, it‚Äôs also growing into a search platform where people go to find their next pair of comfy boots or even business insurance.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-insurance.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok search results for insurance." width="318" height="567" class="aligncenter wp-image-84612 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-insurance.webp 318w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-insurance-168x300.webp 168w" sizes="(max-width: 318px) 100vw, 318px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>TikTok is evolving into a search platform where people learn about a wide range of products and services.</em></p>
<p>Once you‚Äôve optimized your TikTok content, those people will learn that you‚Äôre the solution to what they‚Äôre searching for.</p>
<h3>You can diversify your non-paid traffic</h3>
<p>Google traffic has been a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/2024-google-algorithm-updates">bit wonky lately</a>, to say the least. And with <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ai-overviews">AI Overviews</a> now answering users‚Äô questions, we may see even fewer clicks from that search engine.</p>
<p>TikTok‚Äôs growing user base and its search engine features make it a viable way to generate unpaid traffic to fill some of the Google gap.</p>
<h3>TikTok SEO has a lower barrier to entry than Google SEO</h3>
<p>It‚Äôs really hard for a new brand to show up on Google results pages for highly searched terms. That‚Äôs because Google gives more weight to websites with a high domain authority (something the recent <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-algorithm-documents-leak">Google algorithm document leak</a> seemed to confirm).</p>
<p>On TikTok, however, past performance doesn‚Äôt heavily influence content ranking. So, a brand can appear on TikTok FYPs and search results shortly after posting its first videos. If, of course, the brand uses a smart TikTok SEO strategy.</p>
<div id="what-are-the-tiktok-seo-ranking-factors"></div>
<h2>What are the TikTok SEO ranking factors?</h2>
<p>TikTok‚Äôs algorithm analyzes thousands of ranking signals to decide which posts to place on your FYP and search results. We don‚Äôt know them all, but the good folks at TikTok did <a href="https://newsroom.tiktok.com/en-us/how-tiktok-recommends-videos-for-you/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">publish a document</a> that lists some of the most important ones.</p>
<h3>User interactions</h3>
<p>TikTok personalizes your results based on how you‚Äôve interacted with content previously. This helps ensure you see the most helpful videos (and keeps you on the platform longer).</p>
<p>Here are a few actions that influence TikTok‚Äôs decision:</p>
<ul>
<li>Watching full videos</li>
<li>Following or hiding accounts</li>
<li>Liking or sharing videos</li>
<li>Commenting</li>
<li>Reporting a video as inappropriate</li>
<li>Adding videos to favorites</li>
</ul>
<p>It all starts when you first open the app and tell TikTok what interests you.</p>
<p>Additionally, if other people who share your interests interact with a video, it‚Äôll be more likely to appear in your feed.</p>
<h3>Video information</h3>
<p>These TikTok ranking factors are really important because they‚Äôre the ones you can most directly affect. They include things like:</p>
<ul>
<li>Hashtags</li>
<li>Sounds</li>
<li>Captions</li>
</ul>
<p>When these things in your posts match a search query (and a user‚Äôs activities), your content will appear on their screens.</p>
<h3>Device and settings</h3>
<p>How your device and TikTok account are set up will influence the content you see on the platform.</p>
<p>A few examples of device and settings ranking factors include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Language settings</li>
<li>Country settings</li>
<li>Device type</li>
</ul>
<p>These make sense since content in an unfamiliar language isn‚Äôt going to keep you watching.</p>
<h3>TikTok algorithm weighting factor</h3>
<p>Like most algorithms, TikTok weights some ranking factors more heavily. The idea is to focus more on factors that more directly predict which content will keep users watching.</p>
<p>The takeaway is that your efforts should be on the factors that make your content easier for an algorithm to understand (like adding the right <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/04/07/tiktok-hashtags">hashtags</a>) and those that keep viewers clicking and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/17/how-to-get-more-likes-on-tiktok">liking your posts</a>.</p>
<div id="5-ways-to-improve-your-tiktok-seo"></div>
<h2>5 ways to improve your TikTok SEO</h2>
<p>Now that you know how TikTok SEO works, let‚Äôs get more of your content in front of more people with these TikTok SEO tips.</p>
<h3>1. Find and use keywords</h3>
<p>One of a search engine&#8217;s most basic jobs is matching content to search queries. On TikTok, that means when someone types ‚Äúbeach hats‚Äù into the search bar, TikTok will first look for videos associated with that keyword.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hats.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok search results for beach hats." width="345" height="583" class="aligncenter wp-image-84613 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hats.webp 345w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hats-178x300.webp 178w" sizes="(max-width: 345px) 100vw, 345px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>To appear in these search results, you‚Äôll need to find the right keywords and use them correctly.</em></p>
<p>There are two easy ways to<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/08/09/easy-keyword-research-guide"> research keywords</a> on TikTok. First, type a word relevant to your brand in the search bar and see what TikTok auto-fills.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-search-suggestions-keywords.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok search bar autofill." width="544" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-84614 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-search-suggestions-keywords.webp 544w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-search-suggestions-keywords-480x529.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 544px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>TikTok‚Äôs autofill in the search bar makes keyword research easy.</em></p>
<p>Second, TikTok‚Äôs<a href="https://ads.tiktok.com/business/creativecenter/keyword-insights/pad/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Keyword Insights</a> tool will show you a list of related keywords.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-keyword-insights.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - Keyword Insights page" width="777" height="590" class="aligncenter wp-image-84615 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-keyword-insights.webp 777w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-keyword-insights-480x364.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 777px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>TikTok has a tool to help you find keywords.</em></p>
<p>With a list of keywords in hand, it&#8217;s time to place them strategically. There are several places to do that:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Captions:</strong> Use keywords organically and naturally (meaning, don‚Äôt cram them in if they don‚Äôt make sense) in the captions you write.</li>
<li><strong>Text in video:</strong> You can and should include text for people to read in your videos, and there&#8217;s <a href="https://www.servemethesky.com/blog/tiktok-experiments-seo-trick">some evidence</a> that the algorithm understands keywords in your video text.</li>
<li><strong>Speech in video:</strong> Say your keywords while filming your videos (but again, make sure it‚Äôs organic and not forced).</li>
<li><strong>Hashtags:</strong> We‚Äôll show you how to find great hashtags in the next section.</li>
<li><strong>Bio: </strong>Add your most important keywords to your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/tiktok-bio-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok bio</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Thumbnail text:</strong> TikTok understands the text in your thumbnails, so make sure they include your focus keyword.</li>
</ul>
<h3>2. Go big on hashtags</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/04/07/tiktok-hashtags">Hashtags</a> group content by topic on TikTok so users can find what‚Äôs trending quickly. They‚Äôre also another directional sign that helps TikTok‚Äôs algorithm match content to each user and search query.</p>
<p>Just like keywords, your two jobs here are to find the best hashtags and use them in a way that helps users and algorithms find your content.</p>
<p>Like keywords, one easy way to find hashtags is to type a root word into the search bar. Only this time, complete the search, then tap ‚ÄúHashtags‚Äù at the top.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hashtag-suggestion.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - Hashtag suggestions in TikTok search." width="326" height="576" class="aligncenter wp-image-84616 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hashtag-suggestion.webp 326w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hashtag-suggestion-170x300.webp 170w" sizes="(max-width: 326px) 100vw, 326px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>TikTok graciously gives you a list of related hashtags.</em></p>
<p>You can also do a little <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/competitors-ads">competitive research</a> and see which hashtags others in your space use.</p>
<p>And finally, once again, TikTok has a tool to help you find <a href="https://ads.tiktok.com/business/creativecenter/inspiration/popular/hashtag/pad/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">hashtags in its Creative Center</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hashtag-finder.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - Hashtag finder in TikTok Creative Center." width="867" height="418" class="aligncenter wp-image-84617 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hashtag-finder.webp 867w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hashtag-finder-480x231.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 867px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Just like keywords, you can find active hashtags in TikTok‚Äôs tools.</em></p>
<p>To use your trove of hashtags, just add them to your captions. Here are a few tips to nail that:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use a mix of broad (#FYP; #trending), relevant (#travelwithdogs, #bestpizza), trending (#stpatricksday, #Olympics), and branded (#nike, #youringoodhands) hashtags.</li>
<li>Use three to six hashtags on most posts.</li>
<li>Stick to hashtags that are relevant to your business.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hashtags.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok with lots of hashtags." width="351" height="585" class="aligncenter wp-image-84618 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hashtags.webp 351w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hashtags-180x300.webp 180w" sizes="(max-width: 351px) 100vw, 351px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Use a good mix of different types of hashtags.</em></p>
<p>Remember to include a #[topic]tok hashtag if there‚Äôs a relevant one (like #farmtok, #booktok, or #movietok).</p>
<h3>3. Use trending sounds</h3>
<p>Believe it or not, the sounds you hear while watching TikTok act like hashtags and keywords. When you listen to a few videos with the same catchy beat or funny voiceover, TikTok tends to serve more that use the same sounds.</p>
<p>Plus, you can search for content by their common sounds, just like with hashtags.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-sounds-list.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok search for sounds." width="364" height="577" class="aligncenter wp-image-84620 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-sounds-list.webp 364w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-sounds-list-189x300.webp 189w" sizes="(max-width: 364px) 100vw, 364px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>You can attract a lot of video views with the right sound.</em></p>
<p>We‚Äôll go back to TikTok‚Äôs Creative Center to see which sounds are trending.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-songs.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - Song finder in TikTok Creative Center." width="844" height="392" class="aligncenter wp-image-84619 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-songs.webp 844w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-songs-480x223.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 844px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Look at other accounts in your industry to see which songs best fit the content. To catch their wave, try a few sounds that aren‚Äôt yet trending but show early signs of doing so.</p>
<h3>4. Post at the right frequency and time</h3>
<p>When and how often you post aren‚Äôt direct ranking factors. But both can help your TikTok SEO tangentially.</p>
<p>When you post more often, you simply have more chances to go viral. The<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/20/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok#:~:text=According%20to%20TikTok%2C%20you%20should,need%20Avatar%2Dlevel%20production%20quality."> exact posting frequency is up for debate</a>. TikTok says to post multiple times per day, while other studies say a couple of times per week is enough.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-time-to-post.webp" alt="" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-84621 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-time-to-post.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-time-to-post-480x308.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The real answer is to post as often as you can while still sharing valuable content people want to watch. Remember that video completion <em>is</em> a direct ranking factor, so posting more stuff people won‚Äôt watch all the way through will hurt more than help.</p>
<p>TikTok also doesn‚Äôt directly care<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/09/best-time-to-post-on-tiktok"> when you post your content</a>. But if you get it in front of your audience when they‚Äôre most likely looking at the app, it‚Äôll give your videos a little engagement boost, which may make them more likely to land on the FYP of new potential followers.</p>
<p>Luckily, your TikTok analytics tells you when your followers are flipping through the app.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-analytics-1.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - Screenshot of TikTok analytics dashboard." width="359" height="581" class="aligncenter wp-image-84622 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-analytics-1.webp 359w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-analytics-1-185x300.webp 185w" sizes="(max-width: 359px) 100vw, 359px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Your TikTok analytics dashboard tells you when followers are active. </em></p>
<h3>5. Drive engagement</h3>
<p>Likes, comments, and shares are the real deal ranking factors. You can‚Äôt make people take these actions (thankfully), but you can sure encourage them to do so. Here are a few ways to get more<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/17/how-to-get-more-likes-on-tiktok#:~:text=By%20posting%20videos%20that%20are,Hashtags"> engagement on your TikTok posts</a> for SEO success.</p>
<p>It starts with a great hook to halt those scrolling thumbs. Use a thumbnail and some text that incites curiosity.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hook.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok screenshot with &quot;wait for it&quot; in text." width="344" height="576" class="aligncenter wp-image-84623 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hook.webp 344w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-hook-179x300.webp 179w" sizes="(max-width: 344px) 100vw, 344px" /></p>
<p>Speaking of text, make sure your videos have captions. Many TikTok users binge with the sound off. Captions make sure they can still get what you‚Äôre putting out.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-captions-two.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok with captions." width="366" height="575" class="aligncenter wp-image-84624 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-captions-two.webp 366w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-captions-two-191x300.webp 191w" sizes="(max-width: 366px) 100vw, 366px" /></p>
<p>Then, use some simple tactics like asking people to comment on a statement you make, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/12/14/tiktok-trend-discovery">jumping on new trends</a>, and adding effects to make your posts more interesting.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-effects.webp" alt="TikTok SEO - TikTok with effects included." width="315" height="570" class="aligncenter wp-image-84625 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-effects.webp 315w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/TikTok-SEO-Wordstream-effects-166x300.webp 166w" sizes="(max-width: 315px) 100vw, 315px" /></p>
<h2>TikTok SEO is your key to virality</h2>
<p>TikTok started as a trendy place to share dance moves and silly challenges. It‚Äôs grown way up and now competes with Google as a place where people search <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/tiktok-video-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">videos for inspiration</a>, information, and new brands.</p>
<p>Like Google, you need to optimize your TikTok content and account to reach more people. The good news is that TikTok SEO doesn‚Äôt have to be complicated. Remember to use your keywords effectively and create content people want to engage with. The rest will come with consistency.</p>
