			</item>
		<item>
		<title>TikTok Ads Bidding Strategies (Which Is Best for You?)</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-ads-bidding</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Michelle Morgan]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 06 Jun 2024 14:56:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[TikTok]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=83451</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Here's a quick rundown of TikTok's two ad bidding strategy options and how to choose the right one.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-ads-bidding">TikTok Ads Bidding Strategies (Which Is Best for You?)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Bidding strategies are essential for digital advertising campaigns to ensure you reach your goals. This is undoubtedly true of TikTok, where people increasingly learn about new products and brands.</p>
<p>TikTok only offers two bidding strategy options at the moment: Cost Cap and Maximum Delivery. Although they seem similar on the surface, each provides a unique way to get the biggest bang for your advertising buck.</p>
<p>In this post, we‚Äôll discuss the two bidding strategies available on TikTok and help you determine which is the best option for you.</p>
<h2>The two TikTok ads bidding strategies</h2>
<p>In TikTok ads, your bidding strategy tells the platform how to place bids for your account in the ads auction. (If you‚Äôre new to TikTok ads, read this<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/22/tiktok-ads"> TikTok ads primer</a> on how they work). The goal is to pick the bidding strategy that matches your goal and budget.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Get the free <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteAllStarPlaybook.html?cid=Web_Blog_InContent_TextLink_AllStarPlaybook_Download">All-Star Advertising Playbook</a> to learn how to maximize all of your online marketing strategies.</p>
<h3>Strategy #1: Cost Cap</h3>
<p>Cost Cap bidding is a performance-based approach to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-algorithm">optimization</a>. With Cost Cap bidding, the goal is to control the average cost per result you receive in the auction.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/08/23/tiktok-marketing">The TikTok platform</a> tries to hit an average cost per result based on your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/15/marketing-objectives">campaign goals</a> to make it work. That means that for each conversion, the cost per result might be higher or lower than your target, but the plan is to average out to your goal over time.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tiktok-ads-bidding-wordstream-cost-cap-1.webp" alt="tiktok ads bidding - line graph showing bid cap results." width="865" height="450" class="aligncenter wp-image-83454 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tiktok-ads-bidding-wordstream-cost-cap-1.webp 865w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tiktok-ads-bidding-wordstream-cost-cap-1-480x250.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 865px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Cost Cap bidding is an option for App Install, Conversions, and Lead Generation campaign objectives.</p>
<p>TikTok says this strategy is best for goal-based campaigns and advertisers trying to keep costs around those goals consistent, regardless of market conditions. That‚Äôs because the platform will bid more or less depending on the likelihood of a conversion and won‚Äôt work to spend the budget every single day. If performance isn‚Äôt strong, it will underspend the daily budget for that day, and try again tomorrow when performance may be better.</p>
<p>Now, when it comes to actually setting up your Cost Cap, TikTok suggests setting the highest amount you‚Äôre willing to pay for the conversion. Or for a return on ad spend (ROAS) target, the lowest ROAS you‚Äôre willing to accept. Both of these give TikTok the most leniency when bidding for you in the auction, as they‚Äôre the least restrictive ends of the spectrum.</p>
<p>It also suggests that your budget should be 50 times your Cost Cap bid. While that might be feasible for some folks and is likely where the platform performs best, it may or may not be reasonable for most advertisers. In that case, try to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/10/26/marketing-budget">set your daily budget</a> at least five times your Cost Cap bid, but higher is better.</p>
<p>If you can‚Äôt hit the five-times mark, it&#8217;s not a dealbreaker. I‚Äôve seen campaigns perform well with a Cost Cap at the same level as the daily budget, but it‚Äôs rare. If you‚Äôre in that scenario, you might want to examine your account&#8217;s structure and see if you can condense <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">audiences</a> and budgets to better align with TikTok‚Äôs suggested budget/Cost Cap split.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f44b.png" alt="üëã" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Digital marketing is an always-on strategy. Get a year‚Äôs worth of marketing ideas and tips in the <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite2024MarketingCalendar.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2024MarketingCalendar_Download">Mega Must-Have Marketing Calendar</a>.</p>
<h3>Strategy #2: Maximum Delivery</h3>
<p>Maximum Delivery, unlike Cost Cap, is a spend-based strategy rather than performance-based. You‚Äôre not able to enter a bid amount. Instead, you provide your budget and TikTok will work to drive as many of your<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/05/23/tiktok-ads-targeting"> target actions</a> as possible while spending your entire budget.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tiktok-ads-bidding-wordstream-maximum-delivery-1.webp" alt="tiktok ads bidding - line graph showing Maximum Delivery results." width="867" height="437" class="aligncenter wp-image-83455 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tiktok-ads-bidding-wordstream-maximum-delivery-1.webp 867w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tiktok-ads-bidding-wordstream-maximum-delivery-1-480x242.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 867px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>That means the platform will not pull back on days when your performance is less efficient than others. Your costs could vary quite a bit, but your overall spending will stay level. The only wrinkle is that Maximum Delivery is only available for daily budgets and isn‚Äôt an option if you‚Äôre using a lifetime budget.</p>
<p>You can use this bidding strategy with every campaign objective in the TikTok platform. Just leave the Cost Cap, Bid Cap, Target CPA field in the Bidding &amp; Optimization section empty, and you‚Äôll default to Maximum Delivery for that ad set.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tiktok-ads-bidding-wordstream-bid-control.webp" alt="tiktok ads bidding - screenshot from TikTok ads manager." width="846" height="369" class="aligncenter wp-image-83456 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tiktok-ads-bidding-wordstream-bid-control.webp 846w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/tiktok-ads-bidding-wordstream-bid-control-480x209.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 846px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Like Cost Cap, TikTok recommends setting your budget to achieve 50 conversions per day. Again, this is likely not attainable for many people, so do your best with it.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre seeing good results with Maximum Delivery and want to scale, make sure you do so in a strategic manner. While other platforms like <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/11/28/facebook-ads-benchmarks">Meta ads</a> suggest no more than a 20% budget change on any given day, TikTok says it can handle up to a 50% bid change without seeing performance disruptions. It then suggests you wait until you receive another 50 conversions and at least one day before changing the budget again.</p>
<p>I‚Äôd stick to the 20% rule that Meta suggests here as well (and see how your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/07/facebook-vs-tiktok-ads">Facebook and TikTok ads</a> work together). 50% is a pretty huge increase, and depending on how competitive your industry is, you may see pretty fluctuant CPAs with a larger change.</p>
<h2>Make the best of your TikTok ads bidding strategies</h2>
<p>I‚Äôm a fan of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-seo">TikTok</a> only having two bidding strategies on the platform. It simplifies things and makes it much easier for advertisers to digest and understand.</p>
<p>Are you working on ROAS or CPA targets? Cost Cap is your best option. Are you seeing good results and want to get the most scale from your campaigns? Let‚Äôs hit Maximum Delivery and see how high we can go. Hopefully, this demystifies the TikTok Ads bidding strategies enough for you to feel confident in your campaign settings.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-ads-bidding">TikTok Ads Bidding Strategies (Which Is Best for You?)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>How the TikTok Algorithm Works in 2025 (+9 Ways to Go Viral)</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-algorithm</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rob Glover]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 08 May 2024 12:46:32 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[TikTok]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=82659</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Learn how to use the TikTok algorithm to your advantage so your videos get more views and engagement.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-algorithm">How the TikTok Algorithm Works in 2025 (+9 Ways to Go Viral)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If you post videos and want more people to spend more time watching them, then you and TikTok have a common goal. That‚Äôs why I cringe a bit when I see people talking about hacking the TikTok algorithm for more likes and views.</p>
<p>You don‚Äôt need to trick it; you just need to know how the TikTok algorithm works. Once you understand its basic principles, you‚Äôll know what and when to post for your best shot at TikTok virality.</p>
<p>But what about the <a href="https://now.tufts.edu/2024/04/30/whats-behind-potential-ban-tiktok#:~:text=On%20April%2024%2C%20President%20Joe,American%20firm%20within%20nine%20months." target="_blank" rel="noopener">potential US TikTok ban</a>? TikTok has <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1299807/number-of-monthly-unique-tiktok-users/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">148 million</a> active users in the US. To paraphrase Samual L. Jackson‚Äôs character Nick Fury in Marvel‚Äôs Avengers, ‚ÄúUntil such time as <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">the world</span> TikTok ends, we will act as though it intends to spin on.‚Äù</p>
<p>Let‚Äôs get into the weeds of TikTok‚Äôs algorithm, see how it suggests videos to individual users, and find ways to get your content on more viewers‚Äô screens.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#what-is-the-TikTok-algorithm">What is the TikTok algorithm?</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-does-the-tiktok-algorithm-work-in-2024">How does the TikTok algorithm work in 2025?</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-do-you-reset-the-tiktok-algorithm">How do you reset the TikTok algorithm?</a></li>
<li><a href="#9-ways-to-use-the-tiktok-algorithm-to-your-advantage">9 ways to use the TikTok algorithm to your advantage</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="what-is-the-TikTok-algorithm"></div>
<h2>What is the TikTok algorithm?</h2>
<p>The TikTok algorithm is a recommendation engine that decides which videos to suggest to each individual user.</p>
<p>On TikTok, recommended videos appear on your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/10/07/how-to-get-on-tiktok-fyp">For You Page</a> (FYP) when you first open the app.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-fyp.webp" alt="Tiktok algorithm - screenshot of the TikTok FYP" width="299" height="560" class="aligncenter wp-image-82661 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-fyp.webp 299w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-fyp-160x300.webp 160w" sizes="(max-width: 299px) 100vw, 299px" /></p>
<p>Everyone‚Äôs For You feed is unique and will change over time. TikTok pays attention to the videos you watch, where you post comments, and the accounts you follow. Each interaction is another signal the algorithm uses to refine your FYP‚Äîshowing videos you‚Äôll probably like while keeping videos you won‚Äôt off your feed.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong> Want to grow all of your marketing channels?</strong> Download <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteBestOnlineMarketingTips.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_130marketingtips_Download">The Best Online Marketing Tips for Generating More Traffic, Leads, &amp; Sales</a> to get over 100 actionable growth marketing tactics.</p>
<div id="how-does-the-tiktok-algorithm-work-in-2024"></div>
<h2>How does the TikTok Algorithm work in 2025?</h2>
<p>If you‚Äôve ever sent your friend a cake recipe link because you remembered they love to bake, you get the gist of how the TikTok algorithm works.</p>
<p>Of course, TikTok‚Äôs proprietary algorithm is infinitely more complex than yours (no insult intended). It analyzes thousands of signals to determine which videos belong on your FYP. Let‚Äôs look at a few of the most influential ranking factors.</p>
<h3>Factors TikTok uses to rank content</h3>
<p>We‚Äôll probably never know what every <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-ads-bidding">TikTok</a> ranking factor is, but thanks to <a href="https://newsroom.tiktok.com/en-us/how-tiktok-recommends-videos-for-you" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this post from TikTok</a> itself, we do have an idea of a few ranking categories.</p>
<h4>User interactions</h4>
<p>Your behavior in the TikTok app is the most influential signal for the algorithm. Whenever you like a video or follow a particular account, TikTok uses that to understand your preferences further.</p>
<p>These are some of the user interaction signals TikTok will track:</p>
<ul>
<li>Watching full videos</li>
<li>Following or hiding accounts</li>
<li>Liking or sharing videos</li>
<li>Commenting</li>
<li>Reporting a video as inappropriate</li>
<li>Adding videos to favorites</li>
</ul>
<p>TikTok also uses what you say you are and aren‚Äôt interested in when you first join the app to guide its suggestions.</p>
<p>Other users‚Äô interactions on a video can also determine whether you get it on your feed. If many people who share your interests watch and like a post, there‚Äôs a bigger chance you‚Äôll see it, too.</p>
<h4>Video information</h4>
<p>On the flip side of the equation, TikTok reviews certain characteristics of the videos you‚Äôve interacted with to see how they match your preferences. That‚Äôs important for creators to know since these are the things we have the most control over.</p>
<p>Here are a few of the video and post characteristics the algorithm looks for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Hashtags</li>
<li>Sounds</li>
<li>Captions</li>
</ul>
<p>I‚Äôll go into how to optimize your videos for <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/tiktok-marketing-for-small-businesses/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok marketing</a> using these characteristics in a bit.</p>
<h4>Device and settings</h4>
<p>Device and settings are also user-specific actions the algorithm uses to recommend content. If you‚Äôre registered as a US user, you‚Äôll see a lot more content made in the USA. But unlike user interactions, these are one-time signals that don‚Äôt typically change over time.</p>
<p>A few device and setting signals that may nudge the TikTok algorithm include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Language setting</li>
<li>Country setting</li>
<li>Device type</li>
</ul>
<h4>TikTok factor weighting</h4>
<p>TikTok‚Äôs algorithm weights ranking factors based on how directly they indicate viewer preferences. Direct user actions, like watching a full video, carry much more influence than geographic location.</p>
<p>This means that while it‚Äôs good to be aware of all the ranking factors, your focus should be on posting content that your audience will want to watch and share.</p>
<h3>Factors that don‚Äôt help (and could hurt) your content ranking</h3>
<p>In <a href="https://newsroom.tiktok.com/en-us/how-tiktok-recommends-videos-for-you" target="_blank" rel="noopener">its post</a>, TikTok says it won‚Äôt give creators a boost based on past performance. Someone with a high follower count and previously viral videos won‚Äôt get preferential rankings over a smaller account with more relevant content.</p>
<p>Additionally, there are some types of content that TikTok will de-rank (show less or not at all) in your FYP. These include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Videos you‚Äôve already seen</li>
<li>Content that‚Äôs considered spam</li>
<li>Duplicated content (like a second post of the same video)</li>
<li>Videos with restricted content (like graphic medical procedures)</li>
</ul>
<p>To be clear, some of this content will still be available if you search for it. It just won‚Äôt pop on your FYP.</p>
<div id="how-do-you-reset-the-tiktok-algorithm"></div>
<h2>How to reset the TikTok algorithm</h2>
<p>TikTok‚Äôs algorithm finds the type of content you‚Äôll love based mainly on what you‚Äôve enjoyed in the past. Sometimes, the recommendations don‚Äôt keep up with your changing preferences, and your feed gets stale.</p>
<p>TikTok has built a way for you to scrub its algorithm so it starts from scratch. Then, your interactions moving forward will influence the content you get on your personal FYP.</p>
<p>Here are the steps to <a href="https://newsroom.tiktok.com/en-us/introducing-a-way-to-refresh-your-for-you-feed-on-tiktok-us" target="_blank" rel="noopener">refresh your FYP</a>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Open the TikTok app and tap ‚ÄúProfile‚Äù</li>
<li>Go to the menu at the top and choose ‚ÄúSettings and privacy‚Äù</li>
<li>Tap ‚ÄúContent preferences‚Äù</li>
<li>Tap ‚ÄúRefresh your For You feed‚Äù</li>
<li>Tap ‚ÄúContinue‚Äù and ‚ÄúContinue‚Äù again</li>
</ol>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-refresh.webp" alt="Tiktok algorithm - TikTok refresh screen." width="336" height="581" class="aligncenter wp-image-82662 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-refresh.webp 336w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-refresh-173x300.webp 173w" sizes="(max-width: 336px) 100vw, 336px" /></p>
<p>You can‚Äôt go back once you finish the process. But only your FYP will be affected. Your ‚ÄúFollowing‚Äù feed and profile won‚Äôt change.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4e3.png" alt="üì£" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Free guide &gt;&gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/marketing-with-emotion?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_120WordsPhrases_Download">135 of the Best Words &amp; Phrases for Marketing With Emotion</a></p>
<div id="9-ways-to-use-the-tiktok-algorithm-to-your-advantage"></div>
<h2>9 ways to use the TikTok algorithm to your advantage</h2>
<p>Knowing how the TikTok algorithm works is half the battle. The other half is publishing <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/engaging-posts-on-social-media/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">engaging content</a> that makes it easy for TikTok to find, categorize, and suggest your posts.</p>
<h3>1. Hook viewers quickly</h3>
<p>You have a fleeting second or two to grab a viewer‚Äôs attention and convince them to watch your video. Keep their thumbs from scrolling by adding an attention-grabbing hook that‚Äôs relevant to your audience.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-hook.webp" alt="Tiktok algorithm - Tiktok with a hook in the video cover." width="383" height="582" class="aligncenter wp-image-82663 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-hook.webp 383w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-hook-197x300.webp 197w" sizes="(max-width: 383px) 100vw, 383px" /></p>
<p>A great hook should give the viewer just enough information to make them want more. Try these tactics for your video hooks:</p>
<ul>
<li>Make a bold claim</li>
<li>Ask a question</li>
<li>Share a surprising fact</li>
<li>Hint at a secret</li>
</ul>
<p>Make sure each hook is relevant to your audience, and use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/03/emotional-marketing-copy">emotional words</a> to catch their attention.</p>
<h3>2. Create niche content</h3>
<p>It‚Äôs hard to gain footing with very popular topics on TikTok since many creators are already fighting for precious FYP placement. However, you can use the algorithm to your benefit by finding <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/10/28/niche-marketing">niche</a> topics to post about.</p>
<p>For example, cooking is a super popular topic on TikTok. There are plenty of accounts dedicated to whipping up the best dishes. But Bobby Hicks of <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@retrorecipeskitchen?lang=en-us" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@theretrorecipekitchen</a> uses his account to trial dishes from days of old. Many of the recipes he tests look tasty, while others look like‚Ä¶a veggie gelatin stack?</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-niche.webp" alt="Tiktok algorithm - Screenshot of a TikTok recipe video." width="414" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82664 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-niche.webp 414w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-niche-207x300.webp 207w" sizes="(max-width: 414px) 100vw, 414px" /></p>
<p>It may seem a little odd, but by focusing on one corner of a popular topic, Hicks has grown his account to over 150k followers.</p>
<p>Review the topics you‚Äôd like to use, and if they seem a little crowded, find a subtopic your audience would appreciate. That‚Äôll leave you with fewer competitors in the race for the FYP. It‚Äôll also make your content more relevant to a specific audience, which the algorithm loves.</p>
<h3>3. Use TikTok SEO</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/seo">Search engine optimization</a> isn‚Äôt just for Google. Pretty much any time there‚Äôs a search function, you can optimize your content for it, and TikTok is no exception. Plus, even <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2022/07/12/google-exec-suggests-instagram-and-tiktok-are-eating-into-googles-core-products-search-and-maps/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google admits</a> that TikTok is becoming a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-competitors">popular search engine</a> in its own right.</p>
<p>In addition to the other tips in this guide, you‚Äôll want to use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/articles/keyword-research-for-social-media-guide">keyword research</a> to boost your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-seo">TikTok SEO</a>. Like on search engines, people use specific words and phrases in the search bar to find content on the app. Your job is to figure out what those words are.</p>
<p>Keyword research is easy on TikTok. Make a list of things your audience might search for that are relevant to your business. If you‚Äôre an esthetician, ‚Äúskin care‚Äù might be one of them. Then, enter those words into the TikTok search bar and see what it auto-fills.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-keywords.webp" alt="Tiktok algorithm - TikTok search bar with autofill." width="579" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82665 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-keywords.webp 579w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-keywords-480x497.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 579px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You‚Äôll see options like ‚Äúskin care for men‚Äù and ‚Äúskin care routine.‚Äù Once you‚Äôve gathered a list of keywords, plan out your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-calendar/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content calendar</a> to cover each term. Don‚Äôt forget to add keywords to your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/tiktok-bio-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok bio</a>, too.</p>
<h3>4. Tailor content to the platform</h3>
<p>It‚Äôs smart to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/02/03/repurposing-content#:~:text=Repurposing%20content%20(aka%20finding%20new,Some%20choose%20podcasts%20over%20ebooks.">repurpose content</a> for multiple platforms. But when it‚Äôs time to post it on TikTok, make sure it fits the app‚Äôs best practices.</p>
<p>First, produce and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-edit-tiktok-videos/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">edit</a> full-screen, vertical videos with a 9:16 ratio. That will fill the entire mobile screen while matching how most people view TikTok content.</p>
<p>Second, keep most of your videos short. While there‚Äôs no ideal duration for every video, in 2021, TikTok suggested that the optimal length should be <a href="https://twitter.com/stokel/status/1459171303227904000" target="_blank" rel="noopener">24 to 31 seconds</a>. The platform has <a href="https://www.wired.com/story/tiktok-wants-longer-videos-like-not/?utm_brand=wired-uk&amp;utm_campaign=onsite-share&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_social-type=earned&amp;utm_source=twitter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">pushed for longer content</a>, but many viewers find videos longer than one minute to be stressful, so it&#8217;s safer to keep them under 60 seconds.</p>
<p>Finally, for the best chance of your TikTok videos going viral, keep them positive in tone. <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/hooks-of-viral-tiktoks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Semrush evaluated</a> a large collection of viral TikTok videos and found that those with a positive, funny, or happy vibe did best.</p>
<p>Follow these best practices to get more early engagement, which the algorithm will use as a signal that your video belongs on more FYPs.</p>
<h3>5. Post at the right time and frequency</h3>
<p>The TikTok algorithm doesn‚Äôt really care what time or how often you post‚Äîat least not directly. But it does look at how much engagement an individual video gets. Knowing when and how frequently to post can give your videos a little engagement boost.</p>
<h4>The right time</h4>
<p>The <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/09/best-time-to-post-on-tiktok">best time to post on TikTok</a> depends on when most of your audience will be on the app. The goal is to publish content a little before the peak potential viewing time to get them indexed and ready for your followers.</p>
<p>You can find that information in your TikTok analytics.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-when-to-post.webp" alt="Tiktok algorithm - Graph shown when an audience is on TikTok." width="821" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-82666 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-when-to-post.webp 821w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-when-to-post-480x351.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 821px, 100vw" /></p>
<h4>The right frequency</h4>
<p>Consistency is essential for success on any <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/11/most-popular-social-media-platforms">social media platform</a>. You don‚Äôt want followers to forget about you, and you want more chances to reach new viewers. But how do you quantify ‚Äúconsistency?‚Äù</p>
<p>Just like timing, learning <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/20/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok">how often you should post on TikTok</a> will take some trial and error. TikTok says you should post up to four times per day (of course they do). More realistically, most brands post content to TikTok around two to four times per week (depending on which study you follow).</p>
<p>Here are a few tips to find your perfect TikTok schedule:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Consider your creative capacity:</strong> Posting more often is great, but not at the expense of quality.</li>
<li><strong>Review other creators:</strong> <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/competitors-ads">Spy on your competition</a> to see how often successful accounts in your niche post content.</li>
<li><strong>Watch your analytics:</strong> Vary your posting frequency over several weeks and see how it affects your views and engagement.</li>
</ul>
<h3>6. Incorporate hashtags</h3>
<p>Using <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/04/07/tiktok-hashtags">hashtags on TikTok</a> can help you succeed in two ways. First, hashtags help the TikTok algorithm understand your content so it can better match it to user preferences.</p>
<p>Second, TikTok users use hashtags to search for content, so when your video is tagged, it may show up in their search. As we know, when more people see your content, the algorithm will show it to more people with similar interests.</p>
<p>You can find which hashtags are trending in TikTok‚Äôs <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/login?redirect_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2Fcreator-center&amp;enter_method=redirect&amp;enter_from=creator-center" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Creative Center</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-hashtags.webp" alt="TikTok algorithm - TikTok's Creative Center." width="881" height="478" class="aligncenter wp-image-82667 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-hashtags.webp 881w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-hashtags-480x260.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 881px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Here are a few tips for using hashtags on TikTok:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Don‚Äôt use too many:</strong> One to four hashtags will usually do the trick without making your post look spammy.</li>
<li><strong>Use different types:</strong> Combine branded, topical, popular, and niche hashtags for the best mix of reach and relevance.</li>
<li><strong>Include seasonal and holiday hashtags:</strong> Adding <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/holiday-hashtags-instagram-post-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">seasonal hashtags</a> like #hellospring and #Holloweenscares lets you ride the wave of attention during peak times of the year.</li>
</ul>
<h3>7. Add popular audio clips</h3>
<p>Audio clips work similarly to hashtags on TikTok. If an audio clip gets popular, and you like videos that use that clip, there‚Äôs a greater chance you‚Äôll get more videos with that audio in your FYP.</p>
<p>Head back to the Creative Center to find trending songs.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-audio.webp" alt="TikTok algorithem - TikTok's Creative Center." width="870" height="470" class="aligncenter wp-image-82668 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-audio.webp 870w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-audio-480x259.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 870px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Look in the Popular tab to see which tunes are already getting a lot of play. Then, check out the Breakout tab to catch the next audio wave early.</p>
<h3>8. Add captions</h3>
<p>Many people don&#8217;t watch videos with the sound on. Adding captions to your posts lets those people follow along. But captions don‚Äôt just help you appeal to a broader audience. TikTok‚Äôs algorithm can learn more about your videos from the text of its caption.</p>
<p>TikTok makes it easy to add captions. Tap the Captions icon, and the app will automatically generate them.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-.webp" alt="TikTok algorithem - TikTok's caption manager." width="318" height="568" class="aligncenter wp-image-82669 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-.webp 318w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream--168x300.webp 168w" sizes="(max-width: 318px) 100vw, 318px" /></p>
<p>Make sure you use the keywords you dug up in your video script. The algorithm will read those in the captions and know who should see your videos.</p>
<h3>9. Jump on trends</h3>
<p>One of the best ways to leverage the algorithm to get views is by following <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/12/14/tiktok-trend-discovery">TikTok trends</a>. A trend is a theme, idea, or trait of a video that already has mass appeal. That might be a common song or a dance.</p>
<p>Trends can also be challenges, like this one where one person holds another so they look like they‚Äôre in the iconic scene from the movie Titanic.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-trends.webp" alt="TikTok algorithem - Screenshot of a TikTok video showing the Titanic trend." width="356" height="578" class="aligncenter wp-image-82670 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-trends.webp 356w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/tiktok-algorithm-wordstream-trends-185x300.webp 185w" sizes="(max-width: 356px) 100vw, 356px" /></p>
<p>When viewers get hooked on a trend, TikTok sends them more videos to view. If you&#8217;ve jumped on the trend, the algorithm will put your video in that mix.</p>
<h2>Work with the TikTok algorithm to go viral</h2>
<p>The trick to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/social-media-marketing">social media marketing</a> is remembering that <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/facebook-algorithm">social platform algorithms</a> want you to succeed. If people love the content you post, they‚Äôll spend more time on the app‚Äîwhich is a win-win for everyone.</p>
<p>The key is learning how the TikTok algorithm (and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/instagram-algorithm">Instagram algorithm</a>, for that matter) works to make it your partner in success. Instead of fighting against the algorithm, find ways to leverage it, and you‚Äôll leap-frog ahead of all the accounts trying to trick or hack it. And of course, consider using <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-ads-bidding">TikTok ads</a> to bypass the algorithm altogether.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs a recap of nine ways you can use TikTok‚Äôs algorithm to your advantage:</p>
<ol>
<li>Hook viewers quickly</li>
<li>Create niche content</li>
<li>Use TikTok SEO</li>
<li>Tailor content to the platform</li>
<li>Post at the right time and frequency</li>
<li>Incorporate hashtags</li>
<li>Add popular audio clips</li>
<li>Add captions</li>
<li>Jump on trends</li>
</ol>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-algorithm">How the TikTok Algorithm Works in 2025 (+9 Ways to Go Viral)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
