		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=76100</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Get a boost to your views and followers when you learn how often to post on TikTok.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/20/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok">How Often to Post on TikTok for the Most Views &#038; Followers (+7 Tips to Post Faster)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>On average, a video posted by a business on TikTok gets <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1372502/tiktok-video-views-by-type-account/">17,523</a> views.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-Dunkin.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - TikTok from Dunkin donuts." width="368" height="599" class="wp-image-76102 size-full aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-Dunkin.jpg 368w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-Dunkin-184x300.jpg 184w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Look at all that love for pumpkin spice.</em></p>
<p>Just think of all the brand awareness and engagement you‚Äôll get if you post a dozen times a day!</p>
<p>Not so fast. There is a diminishing return if you bombard the platform with content‚Äîespecially if you‚Äôre pushing out subpar posts for the sake of more views.</p>
<p>The truth is, how often you should post on TikTok depends on a bunch of factors, and it‚Äôs unique to everyone. Your goals, capacity, audience, and industry all come into play.</p>
<p>But TikTok posting frequency does matter‚Äîthe platform loves to serve up fresh, creative content. In this guide, we‚Äôll show you how to figure out the right TikTok schedule for your goals and give you seven tips to keep up the cadence without losing content quality.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#tiktok">How often TikTok says you should post</a></li>
<li><a href="#data">How often the data says you should post on TikTok</a></li>
<li><a href="#ideal">How to find your ideal TikTok posting frequency</a></li>
<li><a href="#tips">7 tips to keep up with your TikTok posts</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="tiktok"></div>
<h2>How often TikTok says you should post</h2>
<p>Let‚Äôs start with what the platform itself tells us about posting frequency. According to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-seo">TikTok</a>, you should post between <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/business/en-US/blog/tiktok-creative-ultimate-guide?redirected=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">one to four</a> times per day.</p>
<p>If that feels like a lot, it is. Especially when you consider that posting <a href="https://later.com/blog/how-often-post-to-instagram/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">three to five times</a> per week on Instagram Reels is the norm.</p>
<p>It‚Äôll help to remember that your videos don‚Äôt need Avatar-level production quality. Even TikTok says that authenticity is more important than big-budget production.</p>
<p>A simple background and your phone‚Äôs camera are enough if you have good information to share.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-simple.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - TikTok from a psychologist." width="432" height="576" class="aligncenter wp-image-76132 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-simple.jpg 432w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-simple-225x300.jpg 225w" sizes="(max-width: 432px) 100vw, 432px" /></p>
<p>Plus, as you‚Äôll learn next, most brands aren‚Äôt posting to TikTok nearly that often.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />TikTok is great, but it‚Äôs not the only way to drum up more sales. Check out this guide to get <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite30BestWaysToPromote.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Marketing_The30BestWaysToPromoteYourBusiness_Download">30 more ways to promote your business</a> (with or without spending money).</p>
<div id="data"></div>
<h2>How often the data says you should post on TikTok</h2>
<p>The more you post, the more content the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-algorithm">TikTok algorithm</a> has to keep people on its platform. So of course, it says to post multiple times each day. But how often do brands post in the real world?</p>
<p>SocialInsider <a href="https://www.socialinsider.io/blog/tiktok-vs-reels-vs-shorts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">conducted a study</a> comparing TikTok to Instagram Reels and YouTube shorts. Three interesting points emerge from the report:</p>
<ul>
<li>Brands post on TikTok about 16 times per month on average.</li>
<li>That‚Äôs just over one post every two days, a far cry from TikTok‚Äôs suggestion.</li>
<li>It‚Äôs still double the pace they post on other short-form video platforms.</li>
</ul>
<p>In another <a href="https://www.rivaliq.com/blog/tiktok-benchmark-report/#title-videos-per-week" target="_blank" rel="noopener">review by RivalIQ</a>, the average brand was only pushing content to TikTok 1.75 times a week. Even the most active brands posted just five times every week, according to that data.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-tiktok-graph-1.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - graph showing how often to post on TikTok" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-76104 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-tiktok-graph-1.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-tiktok-graph-1-480x308.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The takeaway is that you probably don‚Äôt need to hit TikTok‚Äôs posting quota. But you should consider a higher posting frequency than you use on other short-form video platforms.</p>
<div id="ideal"></div>
<h2>How to find your ideal TikTok posting frequency</h2>
<p>We‚Äôve seen that the recommendations and data for how often you should post on TikTok are all over the place. Instead of relying on outside sources to set your schedule, let‚Äôs look at a few ways you can determine the absolute best posting frequency for your unique situation.</p>
<h3>Be real about your creative capacity</h3>
<p>The key to growth on TikTok is landing on the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/10/07/how-to-get-on-tiktok-fyp">For You Page</a> (FYP) of as many viewers as possible. That‚Äôs how new content, and companies, get discovered.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-fyp.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - the FYP on TikTok" width="313" height="567" class="aligncenter wp-image-76105 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-fyp.jpg 313w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-fyp-166x300.jpg 166w" sizes="(max-width: 313px) 100vw, 313px" /></p>
<p>To get there, you have to share content people want to watch. If that means slowing down a little and posting less frequently, that‚Äôs okay. If you push a bunch of posts up that people scroll past, you‚Äôll just have more videos no one sees‚Äîand a bunch of wasted effort for your troubles.</p>
<h3>Consider your type of content</h3>
<p>The type of content you post is an important consideration of your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/08/23/tiktok-marketing">TikTok marketing strategy</a>. Does your audience crave 30-second comedy clips? Or do they want longer Q&amp;As with your team of experts.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-investors.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - Interview TikTok" width="772" height="599" class="aligncenter wp-image-76106 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-investors.jpg 772w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-investors-480x372.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 772px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Those longer videos take more to produce so you‚Äôll be able to post less often. Plus, your viewers might get fatigued with too many deep dives in a week‚Äîwhich could push them to scroll past your multiple posts.</p>
<h3>Review your industry‚Äôs competitiveness</h3>
<p>Some categories like beauty and interior design are <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/11/most-popular-social-media-platforms">more popular on TikTok</a>. That means two things where posting frequency is concerned:</p>
<ol>
<li>There‚Äôs an appetite for more content</li>
<li>There‚Äôs more competition</li>
</ol>
<p>So if you‚Äôre in a busy space on TikTok, you‚Äôll need to nudge your posting schedule up.</p>
<p>Not sure where your industry lands? Look at popular accounts in your field to get the idea. If they‚Äôre <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-get-tiktok-followers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">getting followers</a> with a couple of posts each week, that‚Äôs a good target to start with. If they‚Äôve got two new videos up every day, well, read our tips below to up your posting game.</p>
<h3>Test and track your analytics</h3>
<p>Still not sure how many times you should post on TikTok every week? Just ask your audience. They‚Äôll tell you by way of the <a href="https://www.tiktok.com/creators/creator-portal/en-us/tiktok-content-strategy/understanding-your-analytics/">analytics in your TikTok account</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-analytics.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - screenshot of TikTok analytics" width="323" height="574" class="aligncenter wp-image-76133 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-analytics.jpg 323w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-analytics-169x300.jpg 169w" sizes="(max-width: 323px) 100vw, 323px" /></p>
<p>Try a different cadence each week and watch what happens to total and per-video view count. Also look at your profile views and new follower counts. Those will tell you if people are hungry for more or tired of your posts.</p>
<div id="tips"></div>
<h2>7 tips to keep up with your TikTok posts</h2>
<p>The two things that slow most TikTok creators down are coming up with new ideas and having enough time to shoot and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-edit-tiktok-videos/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">edit each TikTok video</a>. These tips will help you create a pipeline of creative greatness with less time and effort.</p>
<h3>1. Use Duet and Stitch</h3>
<p>One of the worst-kept secrets of successful TikTok creators is that you don‚Äôt have to come up with every novel idea on your own. In fact, TikTok encourages collaboration with two features called Duet and Stitch.</p>
<p>A Duet lets you add your video to an existing TikTok, showing each side-by-side.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image13.png" alt="How often to post on TikTok - screenshot of a TikTok stitch" width="348" height="595" class="aligncenter wp-image-76108 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image13.png 348w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image13-175x300.png 175w" sizes="(max-width: 348px) 100vw, 348px" /></p>
<p>A <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/11/how-to-stitch-on-tiktok">Stitch</a> is similar, but instead of playing next to an existing TikTok, your video plays after it.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image11.png" alt="How often to post on TikTok - screenshot of a TikTok Stitch" width="368" height="599" class="aligncenter wp-image-76109 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image11.png 368w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image11-184x300.png 184w" sizes="(max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px" /></p>
<p>In both cases, you build on an existing, successful video which is way easier than thinking up brand-new concepts.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs an example from PUMA. The brand showed a barista‚Äôs hack for brewing coffee and PUMA‚Äôs hilarious result while trying to copy it.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-Puma.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - TikTok from Puma." width="927" height="530" class="aligncenter wp-image-76110 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-Puma.jpg 927w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-Puma-480x274.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 927px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>2. Work with other brands and creators</h3>
<p>You don‚Äôt have to do all the heavy lifting of social media marketing yourself. Find a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/03/23/how-to-become-a-social-media-influencer">popular creator</a> and let them introduce your brand and products to their audience.</p>
<p>Minute Maid racked up nearly 20,000 likes on this collab with Spencerx.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-influencer-1.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - TikTok from Minute Maid" width="379" height="596" class="aligncenter wp-image-76111 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-influencer-1.jpg 379w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-influencer-1-191x300.jpg 191w" sizes="(max-width: 379px) 100vw, 379px" /></p>
<p>Don‚Äôt worry about finding the biggest TikTok stars. Look for micro-influencers that have an engaged following that would likely love what you do.</p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f44b.png" alt="üëã" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Emotional content is more influential and engaging. Put all the feels in your videos by using these <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite120WordsforMarketingWithEmotion.html?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_120WordsPhrases_Download">135 words and phrases for marketing with emotion</a>.</div></div>
<h3>3. Repurpose content from other platforms</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôre already publishing <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/22/instagram-reels-ideas-for-businesses">Instagram Reels</a> or long-form video content to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/15/youtube-algorithm">YouTube</a>, then you have some assets that‚Äôll speed up TikTok posting.</p>
<p>Take a Reel, tweak it a bit, and repost it on TikTok. Or break apart your 30-minute YouTube tutorial and either post the bits on TikTok or make a trailer that leads people to the full video.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image12.png" alt="How often to post on TikTok - screenshot of a video preview on TikTok" width="324" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-76112 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image12.png 324w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/image12-162x300.png 162w" sizes="(max-width: 324px) 100vw, 324px" /></p>
<h3>4. Use TikTok ads</h3>
<p>Paying for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/08/11/advertising-on-tiktok">TikTok ads</a> won‚Äôt necessarily help you post faster. But it could change how often you should post on TikTok in the first place.</p>
<p>Why? Because with a paid post and the right bid strategy, you can place your content in front of a very <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/05/23/tiktok-ads-targeting">targeted audience</a>. So you could get away with posting less because each ad will be seen by the very people who want to engage with your brand and buy what you sell.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-Hollister-1.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - screenshot of an ad from Hollister" width="398" height="599" class="aligncenter wp-image-76113 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-Hollister-1.jpg 398w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-Hollister-1-199x300.jpg 199w" sizes="(max-width: 398px) 100vw, 398px" /></p>
<p>And if you need inspiration for your ads, just creep <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/14/tiktok-ads-library">TikTok‚Äôs public ad library</a>. You‚Äôll see how other brands tackle TikTok.</p>
<h3>5. Jump on the trend train</h3>
<p>Since its earliest days, TikTok has been all about the trends. Viral dances and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/04/07/tiktok-hashtags">hashtag challenges</a> still rule on the platform. That means there‚Äôs a nearly limitless bounty of creative ideas you are allowed‚Äîeven encouraged‚Äîto copy.</p>
<p>To tap into the next big trend, use <a href="https://ads.tiktok.com/business/creativecenter/inspiration/popular/pc/en?from=001119" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok‚Äôs trend tracker</a> and see what‚Äôs taking over.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-trends.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - screenshot of TikTok's trending chart" width="918" height="492" class="aligncenter wp-image-76114 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-trends.jpg 918w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-trends-480x257.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 918px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You‚Äôll find trending hashtags, songs, and popular videos to fuel your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/01/24/editorial-calendar">content calendar</a>.</p>
<h3>6. Start big and taper</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôve just <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-create-a-tiktok-account/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">created your TikTok account</a>, make a splash by posting as much content as possible early on. That‚Äôll do three things to catapult your success:</p>
<ul>
<li>Give you more chances to land on the FYP</li>
<li>Give the TikTok algorithm plenty of content to index</li>
<li>Give you more data to learn from quickly</li>
</ul>
<p>Try to create enough content to post at least once per day for the first two or three weeks that you‚Äôre on the platform. Then you can taper off to see if your videos are still <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/17/how-to-get-more-likes-on-tiktok#:~:text=In%20this%20article%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20explore%2010%20tips%20for,trends%20and%20leaving%20your%20viewers%20with%20a%20cliffhanger.">getting likes</a> and your follower count keeps growing.</p>
<h3>7. Batch and schedule content</h3>
<p>Assuming your entire job isn‚Äôt creating videos for TikTok, you probably have to jump in and out of the app to edit and post your content. Switching contexts from other tasks to TikTok like that can slow you down.</p>
<p>An alternative is to create posts in batches, then schedule them throughout the week or month. That would gain you some efficiency in your workflow.</p>
<p>Luckily, TikTok has a content scheduler in the desktop version of the app.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-batch-1.jpg" alt="How often to post on TikTok - screenshot of TikTok scheduler" width="810" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-76115 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-batch-1.jpg 810w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok-batch-1-480x356.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 810px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.tiktok.com/business/en-US/blog/introducing-video-scheduler-now-you-can-plan-tiktoks-in-advance?redirected=1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>If you‚Äôre not sure when to schedule content, this guide will help you find <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/09/best-time-to-post-on-tiktok#:~:text=Here%20are%20the%20absolute%20best%20times%20to%20post,a.m.%20on%20Thursday%2C%20and%205%20a.m.%20on%20Friday">the best time to post on TikTok</a>.</p>
<h2>Find your flow on TikTok</h2>
<p>Should you post on TikTok every day? As long as you‚Äôre posting <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/engaging-posts-on-social-media/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">great content</a>, it probably won‚Äôt hurt. But if that cadence burns you out, then take it easy on yourself and spread out your posts. It‚Äôs always better to create and share fewer good posts then more meh ones.</p>
<p>While you‚Äôre figuring out how often you should post on TikTok for your goals, remember these tips to make it easier:</p>
<ol>
<li>Use Stitch and Duet</li>
<li>Work with other brands and creators</li>
<li>Repurpose content</li>
<li>Use TikTok ads</li>
<li>Jump on trends</li>
<li>Start big and taper</li>
<li>Batch and schedule content</li>
</ol>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/20/how-often-to-post-on-tiktok">How Often to Post on TikTok for the Most Views &#038; Followers (+7 Tips to Post Faster)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
