										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There are several reports that collectively reviewed thousands of posts to determine the best average time to post on TikTok. Those stats are interesting, but they‚Äôre not meant to be the foundation of your long-term TikTok strategy.</p>
<p>Why? Because your business isn‚Äôt average.</p>
<p>You have unique customers and followers with their own online habits‚Äîstay-at-home parents don‚Äôt peruse social media at the same time as most restaurant workers. So what really matters is posting your wonderfully creative content to TikTok when <em>your</em> audience will see it (and love it, like it, and share it!).</p>
<p>And that‚Äôs just what we‚Äôll help you do here. By the end of this guide, you‚Äôll be able to make a data-backed determination of the best TikTok posting schedule tailored for your business. Even better, you‚Äôll have a strategy to improve engagement with your posts over time.</p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><h3>Table of contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#matter">Does it really matter what time you post on TikTok?</a></li>
<li><a href="#best">What‚Äôs the best time to post on TikTok?</a></li>
<li><a href="#worst">What‚Äôs the worst time to post on TikTok?</a></li>
<li><a href="#business">How do you find the best time to post on TikTok for <em>your</em> business?</a></li>
<li><a href="#engagement">8 other ways to get more engagement on TikTok</a></li>
<li><a href="#FAQ">The best time to post on TikTok FAQs</a></li>
</ul></div></div>
<div id="matter"></div>
<h2>Does it really matter what time you post on TikTok?</h2>
<p>You bet it does. But only if you‚Äôre posting quality content that‚Äôs relevant to your audience.</p>
<p>It goes like this. Every time someone opens TikTok, the first thing they see is a curated collection of content from new (to them) creators called the For You Page (FYP). <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/10/07/how-to-get-on-tiktok-fyp">Land a spot on the coveted ‚ÄúFor You Page‚Äù</a> and your organic reach goes through the roof!</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-for-you-1.jpg" alt="Best times to post on TikTok - Screenshow of a TikTok post from the For You Page" width="305" height="594" class="aligncenter wp-image-72521 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-for-you-1.jpg 305w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-for-you-1-154x300.jpg 154w" sizes="(max-width: 305px) 100vw, 305px" /></p>
<p>The TikTok algorithm uses two signals to decide what to place on the FYP. The post has to share some characteristics (music, topic, etc.) with content the user previously engaged with. And it needs enough engagement to prove that people will like it.</p>
<p>The second one is where timing comes in. If you post fresh content when your current users are most likely plugged in, it‚Äôll get more early engagement. Then that post has a better shot at being discovered on FYPs.</p>
<p>So don‚Äôt skimp on what you post. But make sure to share it at the right time.</p>
<h2>What‚Äôs the best time to post on TikTok?</h2>
<p>The best time to post on TikTok depends on when your unique audience is thumbing through videos. You‚Äôll learn when that is after posting some content (we‚Äôll show you how in a bit).</p>
<p>But where do you start if you don‚Äôt have data yet? Let‚Äôs use a few recent studies to help us pick times to post your first TikToks.</p>
<p>Each study came up with a slightly different answer. So we‚Äôll triangulate based on all three to get the best options.</p>
<p>Here are the absolute best times to post on TikTok according to each study:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/best-time-to-post-on-tiktok/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hootsuite</a>: 7 p.m. on Thursday</li>
<li><a href="https://sproutsocial.com/insights/best-times-to-post-on-tiktok/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sprout Social</a>: 2 p.m. to 6 p.m. on Tuesday</li>
<li><a href="https://influencermarketinghub.com/best-times-to-post-on-tiktok/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Influencer Hub</a>: 9 a.m. on Tuesday, 12 a.m. on Thursday, and 5 a.m. on Friday</li>
</ul>
<p>That‚Äôs a pretty big spread. But if you look at where things do intersect, we can draw a few conclusions:</p>
<ul>
<li>Weekdays beat weekends by a long shot</li>
<li>Before work and at the end of the traditional workday are safe bets</li>
<li>Tuesday and Thursday are the best overall days to post</li>
</ul>
<p>The results don&#8217;t mean you should only post on Tuesdays and Thursdays. TikTok recommends releasing new content up to four times each day, so plan to spread them around a little. Especially as you learn when your audience is most active.</p>
<h3>Best time to post on TikTok by day</h3>
<p>The Influencer Marketing Hub study is based on 100,000 posts‚Äîmore than the others. So we‚Äôre using it to inform our daily TikTok schedule. Note that these times are all Eastern Standard Time.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/how-to-get-on-tiktok-fyp-best-time-to-post-tiktok.png" alt="best time to post on tiktok" width="720" height="675" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-65211" /></p>
<h4>Best time to post on TikTok on Monday</h4>
<p>6 a.m., 10 a.m., and 10 p.m. are the best times to post on Monday. Seems like people want to wind up their week and wind down their Monday on TikTok.</p>
<h4>Best time to post on TikTok on Tuesday</h4>
<p>2 a.m., 4 a.m., and 9 a.m. are the top times to post on Tuesday. There‚Äôs also particularly high engagement at 9 a.m., so schedule some content then.</p>
<h4>Best time to post on TikTok on Wednesday</h4>
<p>7 a.m., 8 a.m., and 11 p.m. are the best target times for posting on Wednesday. Similar to Monday, people want to start and end their day watching short-form videos.</p>
<h4>Best time to post on TikTok on Thursday</h4>
<p>9 a.m., 12 p.m., and 7 p.m. are your best bets for posting on Thursday. Engagement is high at noon, so it‚Äôs a good time to catch people dreaming about the weekend.</p>
<h4>Best time to post on TikTok on Friday</h4>
<p>5 a.m., 1 p.m., and 4 p.m. rank highest for posting on Friday. That makes sense since people are often doing fun stuff instead of watching TikTok on Friday night.</p>
<h4>Best time to post on TikTok on Saturday</h4>
<p>11 a.m., 7 p.m., and 8 p.m. is when you‚Äôll want to target your first few Saturday posts. Interesting that fewer people are watching early on Saturday. They&#8217;re either up and going or recovering from Friday night.</p>
<h4>Best time to post on TikTok on Sunday</h4>
<p>7 a.m., 8 a.m., and 4 p.m. are the best options for posting on Sunday. That afternoon slot is a good time to help people chase away the Sunday scaries.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs a handy chart to keep it all straight.</p>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th><strong>Day</strong></th>
<th><strong>Best time to post on TikTok</strong></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Monday</td>
<td>6 a.m., 10 a.m., 10 p.m.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Tuesday</td>
<td>2 a.m., 4 a.m., 9 a.m.</td>
</tr>
