<div id="worst"></div>
<h2>When‚Äôs the worst time to post on TikTok?</h2>
<p>Knowing when not to post is as important as knowing when to post. According to Influencer Marketing Hub‚Äôs data, the worst times to post on TikTok are:</p>
<ul>
<li>5 p.m., 6 p.m., and 9 p.m. on any day of the week</li>
<li>10 a.m. to 3 p.m. on Sunday through Wednesday</li>
<li>12 a.m. to 4 a.m. on Friday through Monday</li>
<li>Any time after 9 a.m. on Tuesday</li>
</ul>
<p>Keep in mind that this data is based on worldwide usage. Your results are going to change depending on your audience‚Äôs time zone. In fact, there are several factors to consider as you dial in your own TikTok schedule.</p>
<div id="business"></div>
<h2>How to find the best time to post on TikTok for your business</h2>
<p>The averages above will give you a target to use as you start out on TikTok. But the real magic happens as you gather data from your posts. That‚Äôs when you learn all about your audience&#8217;s habits so you can catch them as they scroll.</p>
<h3>Know your audience</h3>
<p>This is a must in any <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/social-media-marketing">social media marketing strategy</a>. It‚Äôs also really helpful to picture when your potential customers are likely to view your posts.</p>
<p>Start by creating <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/09/23/buyer-personas">personas</a> and then imagining their typical day. When are their busy times, downtimes, bored times, stressed times, and social times?</p>
<p>For example, if your target audience is kids, right after school might be prime time for TikTok. But if working professionals are who you want to engage, lunchtime or late at night is probably better.</p>
<p>Knowing this will help you get a ballpark range as to when they‚Äôre most likely to be on TikTok, as well as what some of the themes in your content should be.</p>
<h3>Access analytics from a Pro account</h3>
<p>A TikTok Pro account is free and easy to set up. Go to your profile, tap the <strong>hamburger icon</strong> in the top right, and select<strong> Privacy and settings</strong>. Tap <strong>Switch to Pro Account</strong>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-setup-pro-account.png" alt="Best time to post on TikTok - screenshots showing how to create a pro account on TikTok" width="720" height="475" class="aligncenter wp-image-72523 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-setup-pro-account.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-setup-pro-account-480x317.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Once you‚Äôre set up, you can access analytics by tapping on that same <strong>hamburger icon</strong>, then <strong>Privacy and settings</strong>, then <strong>Analytics</strong>. These include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Overview:</strong> video views, profile views, and follower count over the past seven or 28 days.</li>
<li><strong>Content:</strong> views from each video in the past seven days, which ones have been on the FYP, and individual insights for each video (more on that soon).</li>
<li><strong>Followers:</strong> top territories, gender, total count, and the holy grail&#8211;peak engagement time.</li>
</ul>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4d7.png" alt="üìó" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Free Guide</strong> <strong><a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite30BestWaysToPromote.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Marketing_The30BestWaysToPromoteYourBusiness_Download">&gt;&gt; The 30 Best Ways to Promote Your Business</a></strong></div></div>
<h3>Learn what time zone your audience is in</h3>
<p>If you run a business based in New York but most of your customers are located on the West Coast, you‚Äôll miss the mark posting for the Eastern time zone. While setting your TikTok schedule, make sure you consider where your audience lives.</p>
<p>The answers will come from your own experience. If you‚Äôre a local service business or you ship the majority of your product to a particular area, you know which time zone to target.</p>
<p>Using this intel, adjust your posting times to the right time zone.</p>
<h3>See when your audience is most engaged</h3>
<p>TikTok analytics also make it easy to tell when your current followers are most active.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-analtycs-user-active-times.png" alt="Best time to post on TikTok - analytics screenshot highlighting when users are active" width="500" height="867" class="aligncenter wp-image-72525 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-analtycs-user-active-times.png 500w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-analtycs-user-active-times-480x832.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 500px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.tiktok.com/creators/creator-portal/en-us/tiktok-content-strategy/understanding-your-analytics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>A word of caution. Just like the research we reviewed before, this data is more of a starting point than a conclusion. Just because your followers are most active at 6 p.m. doesn‚Äôt mean you should always post at 6 p.m.</p>
<p>In his <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zOYXvMGi5_M" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube video on TikTok analytics</a>, Owen Video shares his strategy. If 6 p.m. is peak attention time, he‚Äôll post on TikTok around 1 p.m. That gives his video time to collect engagement and then peak at the perfect point.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-analtyics-prepost.png" alt="Best time to post on TikTok - Analytics graph showing how a post at 1pm is seen at 6 pm" width="480" height="343" class="aligncenter wp-image-72526 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-analtyics-prepost.png 480w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-analtyics-prepost-300x214.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px" /></p>
<p>This is where a little trial, review, and improve comes in.</p>
<h3>Track your best posts</h3>
<p>They always say, ‚ÄúIf it ain‚Äôt broke, don‚Äôt fix it.‚Äù <em>They</em> were probably talking about using your most successful TikTok posts as a guide to when you should post future content.</p>
<p>But you don‚Äôt want to have to check dozens of posts individually.</p>
<p>Luckily, there‚Äôs a nifty way to do this en masse using the <strong>desktop version of TikTok</strong>. Just hover over your profile picture in the top right and click ‚Äúview analytics.‚Äù Then download it all to a spreadsheet.</p>
<p>When you export the data, you‚Äôll get one view to see:</p>
<ul>
<li>Day and time posted</li>
<li>Likes</li>
<li>Comments</li>
<li>Shares</li>
<li>Average watch time</li>
<li>Views</li>
<li>Traffic source (FYP or followers)</li>
<li>Territories reached</li>
</ul>
<p>Look for patterns in your posts that match up to when they were posted. Bonus: you‚Äôll see which types of content are best, too.</p>
<h3>Look at your other social media platform analytics</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôre just starting out with TikTok, you might not have enough data to work with yet. In the meantime, check out the analytics of your other social media channels to see when they‚Äôre most active.</p>
<p>We‚Äôve seen that Instagram and TikTok users are on at different times, so you won‚Äôt be able to mimic the schedule for each. Instead, learn about your audience (who they are, where they‚Äôre from, etc.) on those other channels. And use that info to make a more educated guess about your ideal times to post on TikTok.</p>
<p>You can also use a social <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/01/17/best-free-social-media-management-tools">media management tool</a>. Some include recommended times to post based on past engagement and views.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/best-time-to-post-on-instagram-hootsuite-best-time-feature.png" alt="best time to post on instagram - hootsuite analytics" class="aligncenter" /></p>
<h3>Review your competitors</h3>
<p>No two accounts are the same, but you‚Äôll get a general idea of when to post by looking at accounts that are popular with your target audience. Especially if they‚Äôve been around a while.</p>
<p>It‚Äôs easy to see when each video was posted and how popular it is.</p>
<blockquote class="tiktok-embed" cite="https://www.tiktok.com/@mikekruzich/video/6858390978198277381" data-video-id="6858390978198277381" style="max-width: 605px; min-width: 325px;">
<section><a target="_blank" title="@mikekruzich" href="https://www.tiktok.com/@mikekruzich" rel="noopener">@mikekruzich</a> How to Spy On Your TikTok Competitors For FREE! <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f92b.png" alt="ü§´" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <a title="tiktokgrowthhack" target="_blank" href="https://www.tiktok.com/tag/tiktokgrowthhack" rel="noopener">#tiktokgrowthhack</a> <a title="tiktokgrowthtips" target="_blank" href="https://www.tiktok.com/tag/tiktokgrowthtips" rel="noopener">#tiktokgrowthtips</a> <a title="tiktokgrowth" target="_blank" href="https://www.tiktok.com/tag/tiktokgrowth" rel="noopener">#tiktokgrowth</a> <a target="_blank" title="‚ô¨ original sound - jenn" href="https://www.tiktok.com/music/original-sound-6810498001426041606" rel="noopener">‚ô¨ original sound &#8211; jenn</a></section>
</blockquote>
<p><script src="https://www.tiktok.com/embed.js" async=""></script></p>
<p>These users most likely have their prime posting times nailed down, so ride on their coattails for a bit until you have your own analytics to go by.</p>
<h3>Don‚Äôt forget about seasons and holidays</h3>
<p>Some audiences will behave much differently in summer than in winter‚Äîlike parents with school-aged children. At the same time, online habits on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/04/28/memorial-day-messages" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Memorial</a> or <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/08/12/labor-day-messages-greetings">Labor Day</a> may look more like a weekend than most Mondays.</p>
<p>Keep these temporary changes of behavior in mind when planning the timing and content of your posts. And pay attention to how they affect your results so you‚Äôre even better prepared the next time they roll around.</p>
<div id="engagement"></div>
<h2>8 other ways to get more engagement on TikTok</h2>
<p>Successful TikTok marketing is all about the right content at the right time. We‚Äôve covered the right time, now let‚Äôs talk about the right content.</p>
<h3>1. Go for creative relatability</h3>
<p>People are complicated. We love a surprise but at the same time like familiarity too (<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/04/23/influence-buyers-marketing-psychology">more marketing psychology here</a>). And TikTok seems to be the place where the two come together.</p>
<p>In an <a href="https://www.agilitypr.com/pr-news/public-relations/preparing-for-tiktok-in-2022-3-tips-for-maximizing-the-platform/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">interview with Agility PR</a>, creator Grace Hayes talks about the ‚Äú‚Äôshareable sweetspot,‚Äô combining relatability with something that‚Äôs never been done before. The Internet loves the unexpected.‚Äù</p>
<h3>2. Use the headline approach</h3>
<p>What makes a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/07/17/headline-writing">great headline </a>that draws you in before you skip past it? It strikes a chord by providing just enough information to capture you but not enough‚Äîleaving you to want more and click to get it. Headlines that hook tend to be:</p>
<ul>
<li>Bold claims</li>
<li>Questions</li>
<li>Surprising facts</li>
<li>Emotional</li>
</ul>
<p>And since this is video, throw some music, movement, and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/03/emotional-marketing-copy">emotion</a> in there, and you‚Äôve got your viewers hooked.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-soccor.jpg" alt="Best time to post on TikTok - screenshot of a TikTok with emotion" width="394" height="594" class="aligncenter wp-image-72527 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-soccor.jpg 394w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-soccor-199x300.jpg 199w" sizes="(max-width: 394px) 100vw, 394px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@moneycoachvince/video/7055268544241650990?is_from_webapp=1&amp;sender_device=pc&amp;web_id6992965571860104710" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>Here are some <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/01/headline-examples">headline examples and templates</a> to inspire your TikTok videos:</p>
<ul>
<li>X things about ____ you wish you knew sooner</li>
<li>Why/how to ____ even if you _____</li>
<li>The truth about ______</li>
<li>This is why I don‚Äôt _______.</li>
<li>Everything you know about _____ is wrong.</li>
</ul>
<ol start="3"></ol>
<h3>3. Don‚Äôt just dance</h3>
<p>A <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/hooks-of-viral-tiktoks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">study by Semrush</a> found that while popular dance videos receive more plays than other genres, they also receive fewer shares and comments. In fact, &#8220;more than 1 in 3 viral TikTok videos focused on a person speaking within the first three seconds.&#8221;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-SEMrush-viral-stats.jpg" alt="Best time to post in TikTok - Graph showing the most popular TikTok formats" width="723" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-72529 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-SEMrush-viral-stats.jpg 723w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-SEMrush-viral-stats-480x398.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 723px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>4. Shorter is still often better</h3>
<p>TikTok continues to increase the allowable length of videos on its platform (it‚Äôs now up to 10 minutes). While you can and should experiment with longer-format content, the conventional wisdom‚Äîas <a href="https://www.wired.com/story/tiktok-wants-longer-videos-like-not/#:~:text=By%20November%202021%2C%20the%20optimal%20recommended%20video%20length,had%20doubled%20to%20between%2021%20and%2034%20seconds." target="_blank" rel="noopener">suggested by TikTok in 2021</a>‚Äîis that videos between 21 and 34 seconds are best.</p>
<p>TikTok Live, of course, is an exception. You can <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/01/how-to-go-live-on-tiktok">learn how to go live on TikTok here</a>.</p>
<h3>5. Stay positive</h3>
<p>Yes, it&#8217;s important to lead with emotion. But on TikTok, that emotion should be happy, positive, or funny. That same study by Semrush found that 58% of viral videos skewed towards humor and happiness.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-graph-genres.png" alt="Best time to post in TikTok - Graph showing the most popular TikTok grenres" width="720" height="574" class="aligncenter wp-image-72530 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-graph-genres.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-graph-genres-480x383.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>6. Get into a rhythm (pun not intended)</h3>
<p>The more videos you post, the more likely you are to show up on someone‚Äôs FYP right? Yes and no. TikTok recommends posting 1-4 times per day. But don‚Äôt just post just to post. Find a format, theme, or genre that people like and that you can create variations on. Then only post when you have crowd-pleasing content. You can get even <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/tiktok-marketing-for-small-businesses/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">more TikTok marketing tips here.</a></p>
<h3>7. Hop on trends/challenges</h3>
<p>Going against the grain isn‚Äôt the name of the game on TikTok. Use viral sounds, participate in challenges, do the duets, embrace it all. TikTok songs are like Instagram hashtags. They are portals to endless threads of videos that just may lead a viewer to yours. And use hashtags too.</p>
<h3>8. Don‚Äôt try too hard</h3>
<p>At the end of the day, TikTok is a place for happiness, humor, and relatability. Forcing any one of these things has the opposite effect. Don‚Äôt stress, be yourself, and actually have fun. This will reflect in your content and resonate with viewers.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-tries-too-hard-1.jpg" alt="Best times to post on TikTok - screenshot of a TikTok joking about people who try too hard" width="392" height="594" class="aligncenter wp-image-72531 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-tries-too-hard-1.jpg 392w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/TikTok-times-TikTok-tries-too-hard-1-198x300.jpg 198w" sizes="(max-width: 392px) 100vw, 392px" /></p>
<div id="FAQ"></div>
<h2>When to post on TikTok FAQs</h2>
<p>A lightning round of Q&amp;A to help you pick the best times to post on TikTok.</p>
<h3>Does posting time matter on TikTok?</h3>
<p>Yes, as long as your content is already good quality and relevant. Posting at the optimal times helps you gain early <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-localiq-brand-amplifier-works/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">engagement</a> which increases the chances that your posts land on the <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/what-is-fyp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok FYP</a>.</p>
<h3>How often should you post on TikTok?</h3>
<p>TikTok recommends that you post between 1 &#8211; 4 times per day. Just like posting times, post frequency will be individual to your business and audience. Test out more and fewer posts to find the sweet spot. But prioritize quality over quantity‚Äîposting more bad content will hurt your business faster.</p>
<h3>How do you get popular on TikTok?</h3>
<p>Picking the right times to post is one step. But for a business to get popular on TikTok you‚Äôll need to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/social-media-marketing-trends/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">follow trends</a>, have a great strategy, and post <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/engaging-posts-on-social-media/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">scroll-stopping content</a>. You‚Äôll get a boost if you also <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/tiktok-ad-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">use paid TikTok ads</a>.</p>
<h2>When‚Äôs the best time to post on TikTok? [Recap]</h2>
<p>TikTok has a large audience and high organic reach. To engage as many people on the platform as possible, you‚Äôll need to post the right content, at the right frequency, at the right time.</p>
<p>Finding the right time for your business to post on TikTok will take some testing. But before you have data, you can aim for the best average time, which is Tuesdays and Thursdays, before and after the traditional workday.</p>
<p>After you have some posts gathering interest, use TikTok analytics to find trends and learn about your audience. Test fewer and more frequent posts. Try different days and times. Keep track by downloading the results from your TikTok pro account on your desktop.</p>
<p>But most importantly, just start posting. There‚Äôs an engaged audience just waiting for your brand of brilliance‚Ä¶don‚Äôt leave them hanging!</p>
<p><strong>Want more best times?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/12/01/best-time-to-post-on-instagram">The Best Time to Post on Instagram [For Every Scenario]</a></li>
